				\begin{document}$$\mu ={\mu }_{0}\exp (\alpha \sqrt{E})$$\end{document}here μ0 is the zero field mobility, α is Pool-Frenkel parameter and E is electric field strength. Such mobility dependence is explainable by terms of the Borsenberger and Weiss30, and Borsenberger et al.31 disorder formalism. The mobility defining parameters μ0 and α values as well as the mobility value at the 6.4 × 105 V cm−1 field are given in Table 2.
